# Design System — No New Styles

CoachingBoard uses a three-tier CSS token system. All UI work **must** reuse existing tokens and patterns. Do not invent inline colors, hard-coded hex values, or new CSS classes for things the design system already handles.

## CSS Custom Properties (tokens)

Always use these — never hard-code colors:

| Token | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `var(--pt-bg-toolbar)` | Toolbar / bar backgrounds (top, bottom, sidebar) |
| `var(--pt-bg-surface)` | Card / dialog / dropdown backgrounds |
| `var(--pt-bg-body)` | Page / field background |
| `var(--pt-bg-primary)` | Input / code block background |
| `var(--pt-text)` | Primary text |
| `var(--pt-text-muted)` | Secondary / placeholder text |
| `var(--pt-text-white)` | Text on dark/colored backgrounds |
| `var(--pt-border)` | Button hover backgrounds, dividers |
| `var(--pt-accent)` | Focus rings, active indicators, links (dark surfaces) |
| `var(--pt-danger-hover)` | Active/pressed tool state (the red) |
| `var(--pt-danger-lightest)` | Danger text on dark backgrounds |
| `var(--pt-success-hover)` | Confirm / success button background |
| `var(--pt-btn-primary)` | Primary action button background; also links + focus rings on **light surfaces** (5.17:1 on white — use instead of `--pt-accent` which only meets 2.6:1 on white) |
| `var(--pt-btn-primary-hover)` | Hover state for primary action buttons and links on light surfaces |
| `var(--pt-bg-inverted)` | White surface (dialogs, side-sheets) |
| `var(--pt-text-on-inverted)` | Dark navy text on white/inverted surfaces (17:1 on white) |
| `var(--pt-border-on-inverted)` | Subtle **container/card** border on white (`rgba(0,0,0,0.12)`, ~1.2:1) — do **not** use for interactive element borders (inputs, buttons), which need `rgba(0,0,0,0.45–0.5)` to meet WCAG 1.4.11 (3:1) |

## Button patterns

Match exactly — do not deviate:

```css
/* Normal button (toolbar/sidebar) */
background: var(--pt-bg-surface);
border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.25);
border-radius: 6px;
color: var(--pt-text);

/* Hover */
background: var(--pt-border);

/* Active / aria-pressed="true" tool */
background: var(--pt-danger-hover);
border-color: var(--pt-danger-hover);
color: var(--pt-text-white);

/* Focus ring — dark surface */
outline: 2px solid var(--pt-accent);
outline-offset: 2px;  /* or -2px/-4px for inset (menus, sidebar) */

/* Focus ring — light/inverted surface (dialogs, side-sheets, toasts) */
/* --pt-accent is only 2.6:1 on white; use --pt-btn-primary (5.17:1) instead */
outline: 2px solid var(--pt-btn-primary);
outline-offset: 2px;
```

## Toolbar bars

All horizontal bars (top context, bottom) share:
- `background: var(--pt-bg-toolbar)`
- `box-shadow: 0 -2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.3)` (bottom) or `0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.3)` (top)
- `min-height: 52px` — never let a bar change height dynamically

## Sidebar

- Same `var(--pt-bg-toolbar)` background as bars
- Tool button size: **44×44px** — primary tool palette buttons use this larger target
- Active tool: `var(--pt-danger-hover)` background (red)
- Hover: `var(--pt-border)` background

## Touch target sizing

CoachingBoard targets **WCAG 2.1 AA** — not AAA. Apply the right threshold based on context:

| Context | Minimum | Standard |
|---|---|---|
| Primary controls (sidebar tool palette, dialog buttons, main action buttons) | **44×44px** | WCAG 2.5.5 AAA — chosen as project standard for primary actions |
| Secondary controls (inline formatting toolbars, compact toggles, icon-only row actions) | **24×24px** | WCAG 2.5.8 AA |

Do not flag secondary toolbar buttons (e.g. notes formatting toolbar, context editor) as failing touch target if they meet the 24×24px AA minimum. Reserve the 44px expectation for the sidebar and full-height action buttons.

## Dialogs / panels

See `cb-dialogs.ts` and `cb-share.ts` for the canonical dialog CSS — reuse `.dialog-header`, `.dialog-body`, `.confirm-actions`, `.cancel-btn`, `.confirm-success` patterns.

## CSS in static styles, not inline

All styles belong in the component's `static styles = css\`...\`` block. Never use `style="..."` attributes in templates except for dynamic values that cannot be expressed as CSS (e.g. `style="--playback-progress: ${t}"`).

```ts
// ❌ Inline style
html`<div style="background: var(--pt-bg-toolbar); border-radius: 6px;">`

// ✅ Named class in static styles
html`<div class="my-panel">`
// + in static styles:
// .my-panel { background: var(--pt-bg-toolbar); border-radius: 6px; }
```

The one allowed exception: CSS custom properties set dynamically at runtime (e.g. `style="--panel-w: ${width}px"`).

## What NOT to do

```css
/* ❌ Hard-coded colors */
background: #1a1a2e;
color: rgba(78, 168, 222, 0.08);
border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.08);

/* ❌ New utility classes */
.menu-nav-light-hover { ... }
.sidebar-active-red { ... }

/* ✅ Use tokens */
background: var(--pt-bg-body);
background: var(--pt-accent);   /* at low opacity if needed */
border: 1px solid var(--pt-border);
```

## Before adding any CSS

1. Search existing component styles for the same visual pattern
2. Use the token from the table above
3. If a token doesn't exist for your use case, check `index.html` where all tokens are defined — the value is already there
